@NODE "Introduction" "So what does this program do then?"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
Hi and welcome to this fantastic util !  This little program will let you do
a  few  little things to animations that include scaling down the animation,
so  that  it  can  be  played in SFMV format size.  Also you can reverse the
animation  ( If you want to ) and peform an effect on the animation ( If you
want to ).

The  results  from  this  util will be saved out as IFFs.  This will let you
combine  them back into an anim using utils such as DPaint (tm) or Animbuild
amongst others.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Loading" "Feed the beast"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
Loading  of  a animation is simple, just click on the file request gadget in
the @{FG SHINE}`Animation'@{FG TEXT} loading area of the main window, or if you feel up to it you
could type in the filename and path of it in the string gadget next to it !

If  the  file  selected is valid, then it will be loaded into memory and the
information about it will pop up in the animation window.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Saving" "They know"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
Saving is just as simple as loading.  Use the file requestor gadget thing to
select  a  `base' filename (or type it in the string gadget).  The @{FG SHINE}'save as'@{FG TEXT}
cycle  gadget  will  let  you  pick  whether  to  save  the results as @{FG SHINE}`base
filename+number'@{FG TEXT}  or  @{FG SHINE}`frame  number+base filename'@{FG TEXT}.  The loop frame gadget
will  let  you  use  or lose the loop frames in some animations ( DPaint and
Brilliance produce loop frames ).

If  there is a error in the save path then it will pop up when you decide to
process the animation !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effects" "Fun time"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
In  the effects area of the window you will see a list of effects with which
to  process  the  animation  with.   The  effects  included  in this version
include;


	SFMV Animation Tool Effects ( Version 1.1 )
	  @{"  No operation           " link "Effect_NoOpp"}- Do nothing
	  @{"  Jump line              " link "Effect_JumpLine"}- Remove `stray' pixels
	  @{"  Random box             " link "Effect_RandomBox"}- Water colour the anim!
	  @{"  Center point           " link "Effect_CenterPoint"}- Remove some `detail'
	  @{"  Hg pixel to Lw colour  " link "Effect_HgToLw"}- Improve run length compression
	  @{"  Hg pixel to Hg colour  " link "Effect_HgToHg"}- Improve run length compression

After you have selected an effect, and you push the process gadget, you will
be  presented  with a parameter window for the effect in question ( That is,
if  the effect needs prameters ).  Each effect that has options will present
you  with a do effect option that will accept the parameters already set and
perform the effect.

The  effect selected will pop up in the string gadget under the effect list.
The best way to find out what each one will do is to try them out !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Controls" "Dem dar controls"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
In the control area of the window you are presented with a number of gadgets
that will let you control how the program will work !

Hitting the Sublime logo will pop up an about window.

Pushing  the  @{FG SHINE}'display  animation'@{FG TEXT}  button will display the currently loaded
anim.

Toggling  the  show  work/progress gadget will ( When you process the anim )
show the work or a progress bar !

Hitting  the  save whole image gadget will toggle between the different size
images that will be saved.  The save whole image option will let you process
&  save  the whole image.  The save scale SFMV PAL/NTSC options will let you
scale the whole image down into 160x128/100 size for SFMV convertion !
The  save  SFMV  PAL/NTSC will chop out a image the size of SFMV PAL or NTSC
with no scaling of the image !
The  forward  save  gadget will let you save the animation frames in forward
order (i.e.  normal) or reverse order ( Can be usefull for a few effects !).

The  process  gadget  when  pushed  will  set the program off to perform the
chosen  effect  on the chosen animation and saving the results to the chosen
base path !

Please  note  that  before  you can push the process gadget, you must have a
animation loaded, a save path selected and an effect selected.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_NoOpp" "No operation effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
The no operation effect will not do a single thing to the animation.  It has
been added so that you can scale down animations to the SFMV size.

Also it lets you reverse an animation amongst other things!
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_JumpLine" "Jump line effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
When the jump line effect is selected, a parameter window will pop up.  This
effect was added to improve the compression on the data with as little image
`loss'  as  possible  !   It  works by scanning the image, when it finds two
pixels  that  are  the same colour it will draw a line between them, killing
all pixels in between !

The  direction gadget in the effect window will let you set the direction of
the effect scan.  Setting it to X will scan left to right and a setting of Y
will  scan from top to bottom.  The skip gadget is to set the maximum length
of a jump line.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_RandomBox" "Random box effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
This  effect  will  let  you  process the animation into a water colour type
effect.  The prameters are easy enough to understand so there is very little
point  in  writing  about them here!.  If you don't understand then just try
the effect out a few times and then you will understand !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_CenterPoint" "Center point effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
This is the same effect as the @{"Jump line" link "Effect_JumpLine"} effect.  However this one will plot
a pixel in between the two matching points, rather than drawing a line.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_HgToLw" "High pixel to low colour effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
This  effect will count the amount of pixels used in the animation, and then
repmap  the  most used to the lower end of the palette.  The least used will
be  re-mapped  to  the higher end of the palette.  This effect can help with
compression !

The  options on offer in this effect are to do with how the main pixel count
is made up.  You can pick to use the whole, half or quater of the animation.
Please note that whole option will take longer then half and so on !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Effect_HgToHg" "High pixel to high colour effect"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /	    @{fg text}SFMV Anim Tool Version ╣À╣@{fg shine}
 //	  \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~	\/	\/	   \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
This  is  the  same as the @{"Hg pixel to Lw colour" link "Effect_HgToLw"} effect, but in this one the
most  used  colour will be mapped to the higher colours and the least to the
lower colours.
@ENDNODE
