Sublime :  sab-lim', adj.  set aloft (passing into adv.) :  lifted on high :
exalted  :   lofty :  majestic :  elate :  blindly supercilious :  supreme :
of  the highest or noblest nature :  awakening feeling of awe and veneration
:   (amat.)  just  under the skin.-n.  that which is sublime :  the lofty or
grand  in thought or style :  the supreme degree.-v.t.  to raise aloft :  to
exalt :  to transmute into something higher.
		- Chambers's twentieth century dictionary (revised edition).

